# JavaScript Program to Remove Duplicates from an Array

Here are several methods to remove duplicated elements:

## Method 1: Using `Set` (Simplest & Most Efficient)
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [...new Set(arr)];
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 2: Using `filter()` with `indexOf()`
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.filter((item, index) => arr.indexOf(item) === index);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 3: Using `reduce()`
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.reduce((unique, item) => 
  unique.includes(item) ? unique : [...unique, item], []
);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 4: Using `forEach()` with Object
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [];
const seen = {};

arr.forEach(item => {
  if (!seen[item]) {
    seen[item] = true;
    uniqueArr.push(item);
  }
});
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 5: Using `Map`
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [...new Map(arr.map(item => [item, item])).keys()];
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Performance Comparison

| Method | Performance | Use Case |
|--------|-------------|----------|
| **Set** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Fastest | Best choice - simple & efficient |
| **filter()** | ⭐⭐⭐ Good | Simple, readable |
| **reduce()** | ⭐⭐⭐ Good | Functional approach |
| **forEach()** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Fast | Good alternative |
| **Map** | ⭐⭐⭐ Good | Less common |

## Recommendation
**Use Method 1 (Set)** - It's the fastest, most concise, and most readable solution:

```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [...new Set(arr)];
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

